Pin `kernels` package version to work around transformers 5.x runtime breakage.

transformers/integrations/hub_kernels.py:89 constructs `LayerRepository("cuda", …)`
at module load time without a `revision=` or `version=` argument. The `kernels`
library made this required in 0.13.0 (2026-04-10), so any newer install raises:

  ValueError: Either a revision or a version must be specified.

The error fires the first time anything imports transformers.activations — which
SGLang does very early via `_apply_hf_patches() → modeling_llama`. Symptom:
SGLang head/worker exits immediately on startup.

transformers 5.8.0 declares `kernels<0.13,>=0.12.0` only in `extras_require`
([kernels], [integrations], [all], [dev]) — NOT in core install_requires —
so plain `pip install transformers==5.8.0` does not enforce the cap. Whatever
version of `kernels` happens to be in the env wins. As of 2026-05-29 the latest
on PyPI is 0.15.1 (released same day), which is what fresh builds grab.

Fix: force-reinstall the last <0.13 release after the transformers step.
KERNELS_VERSION="0.12.3" is the highest safe version. Empty string means
"don't touch", preserving upstream behaviour on builds that don't need this.

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly in the local clone of
scitrera/cuda-containers, AFTER dockerfile-sm121.patch (which has already
moved the sglang install to the end of the builder stage).

Remove when transformers ships a hub_kernels.py call that passes the new
required revision/version arg upstream.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -243,6 +243,18 @@ RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
         uv pip install -U transformers --pre; \
     fi

+# dgxarley: pin huggingface `kernels` to a transformers-5.x-compatible
+# version. transformers/integrations/hub_kernels.py:89 calls
+# LayerRepository("cuda", …) without revision=/version=, which kernels>=0.13
+# rejects at module import time, killing SGLang startup. See
+# patches/dockerfile-kernels-pin.patch for the full root cause.
+ARG KERNELS_VERSION=""
+RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
+    if [ -n "$KERNELS_VERSION" ]; then \
+        echo "=== Pinning kernels==${KERNELS_VERSION} (transformers-5.x compat) ==="; \
+        uv pip install --force-reinstall --no-deps kernels==${KERNELS_VERSION}; \
+    fi
+
 # SM121 (DGX Spark GB10) shared memory fix for cutlass_moe_fp4.
 # Patches run_fp4_blockwise_scaled_group_mm_sm120() in the JIT-compiled
 # nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh to use KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecializedCooperative
